<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">SOWPODS vs TWL: Loanword Differences</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">92K</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">More words in SOWPODS</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Many</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Are loanwords</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Check</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Before tournament play</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>If you study loanwords for SOWPODS tournaments, be careful — many won't work in TWL games. Words like JEUX (French, games) and ZAX (a slate-cutting tool) are SOWPODS-only. Always confirm which dictionary your event uses before relying on borrowed vocabulary.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips for Loanwords</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Know your dictionary:</span> If playing SOWPODS (international), you have access to thousands more loanwords than TWL. Words like JEUX, QAIDS, and ZAX are SOWPODS-only. Always confirm which dictionary your game uses.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Memorise short loanwords:</span> Two and three-letter loanwords like QI, ZA (pizza), KA (Egyptian spirit), and TAO provide enormous flexibility for parallel plays and tight board positions.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Challenge bluffs confidently:</span> Opponents may play fake foreign-sounding words hoping you won't challenge. If a word looks like a loanword but you've never seen it in study lists, challenge it.</p>
  </div>
</div>

